rComments: I can tell 100% that Professor Yung wants his students to be successful (very rare in UofT). He reply email fast and with great detail. He even gave us his phone number in class and asked us to call if we have questions. A very good man!

It was very nice that the instructor provided a lot of assistance outside of the lectures. The excel spreadsheet along with the videos were very helpful. The lecture notes could be more detailed since the textbook was very long and hard to follow along as it was in a different format than the lecture slides.
The course requires attendance. If you don't go to class you will be lost.
The class average for the midterm was in the 80s. Accounting is easier to understand than finance.

He is a good person and a terrible teacher. Had no logic at all. Every class he just threw tons of formulas at us without properly explaining them. DO NOT TAKE JRE300 IN SUMMER! In winter/fall you have other instructors to choose from.
He may seem good when explaining easy stuff, but when things got complex he became useless. 0 out of 10.
Provides handouts and examples in class to illustrate concepts. You should attend class to save yourself time.
If you dont read the textbook prior to his lecture, you will definitely get lost.

I was nervous about finance in general but ended up loving it over the summer. Plus, I'm glad I don't have to worry about in the full-year with Tanya. The quizzes were the easiest, the mid-term was fair, and the exam was brutal. He cares for the students and approachable out of class. By far one of best professors in UTM.

Professor Otto is an amazing professor. Unlike most of the other professors at U of T, he wants all of his students to succeed and take something new from each and every lecture. The tests are all fair, and you'll do well if you pay attention in class.

Professor Young is by far the most caring professor at Rotman. He is a good lecturer but can be very boring at times since he is so soft spoken and speaks in monotone. He takes a genuine interest in each student and wants them to succeed. He marks very fairly (B- average) and leaves nothing to surprise on test/exams. Attend to succeed.

Had Professor Yung for RSM333, RSM435 and RSM432. Hands down the nicest professor in all of Rotman undergrad. Really friendly and easy to approach. He was always happy to answer questions outside of class.

Quiz was easy, assignments were ok, but midterm and final exam were super hard. Although students were allowed to use cheat sheet in midterm and final, it did not provide much help. Final is very different to the past exams. He is a nice professor anyway, his way of teaching is better than Tanya in my opinion.
Core course...
Course includes simulations.

Has held special office hours over the weekend so his students can better prepare for the midterm. He has also held additional optional tutorials in addition to the regular tutorials offered by the TA and himself.
Provides detailed solutions for the models while learning in class.
He is fair. He wants to ensure his students are as competitive with other programs/schools. He is available to answer questions and responds quickly to e-mails.
He has held office hours and was available for optional tutorials as well.

Avoid taking his class by all means. If you're looking for a nice professor, then go ahead, but he is a very bad teacher that does not really care about the success of his students. Do not get me wrong, he is very knowledgeable and polite, but you will learn everything on your own.
Super nice prof
Very detailed presentations. Concepts were explained clearly in lectures. One of the nicest finance profs.
He's the best!
midterm was a breeze, good luck with the exam. nice prof!

Material Taught often  Material Tested Assignments very fend- for-yourself (figure out what he's asking for yourself) Highly ambiguous questions on assignments  BUT material is not too hard to teach yourself. He complicated this class for me very much, when the material truly wasn't hard. Oh, and don't bother trying to write notes during lec.

Otto can be confusing teaching the subject matter, but his examples and test questions are very straight forward. Always there to help if needed (although nobody needed him) I showed up for 1 out of 10 classes and he remembers who I was and asked how I did after the final exam and how I felt about the course. A very kind person in general who cares

Otto has real experience in the finance industry and only expects students to know the basic fundamentals and what's necessary. He doesn't play mind games and write tests questions that read like stories like certain other finance profs.  He's also extremely helpful and down to earth easily approachable. However, his lectures can be a bit dull.
Very Helpful & easy to approach

Very nice guy and approachable! Very detailed lectures, although can be a bit dull and confusing due to the subject matter. Tests are very long, but fair. Always there for extra help and even gave us his number to text. Assignment was a little confusing though, but still more practical than some of the other profs.

Really helpful prof, very enthusiastic about finance. He makes sure his sections are very well prepared for the midterm and final exam. His lecture slides are very detailed and available online too. Best prof I've ever had! Make sure you go to the tutorials as well to get extra instruction for the assignments.
